# Cursor Rules -- SaaS-Viber Project

## Stack
- React + TypeScript + Vite
- Tailwind CSS with CSS custom properties for theming
- shadcn/ui (Radix UI primitives) for accessible components
- Design tokens in docs/design/tokens/tokens.json

## File Structure
- src/components/ → UI components (ui/ for shadcn base, feature dirs for custom)
- src/pages/ → Route-level components
- src/hooks/ → Custom hooks (useAuth, useTheme, etc.)
- src/lib/ → Utilities and API clients
- src/contexts/ → React context providers
- src/types/ → Shared TypeScript types
- src/styles/ → Global CSS and theme variables

## Code Style
- PascalCase for components (UserProfile.tsx)
- camelCase for hooks (useAuth.ts) and utils (formatCurrency.ts)
- Use @/ path alias for src/ imports
- One component per file
- TypeScript strict mode -- no `any` types
- Tailwind utility classes -- no inline styles
- All colors via CSS custom properties, never hardcoded hex

## Design System
- 4px spacing grid (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64)
- WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratios (4.5:1 text, 3:1 UI)
- 44x44px minimum touch targets
- Skeleton loading states over spinners
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion for all animations
- Light + dark mode via class strategy on html element

## Component Rules
- Wrap shadcn/ui components to extend -- never modify base ui/ files
- Include TypeScript props interface on every component
- Add ARIA labels and keyboard navigation
- Handle loading, error, and empty states
- Use Radix UI primitives for overlay/menu/dialog patterns

## Architecture References
- docs/architecture/DOMAIN_MODEL.md → Data model
- docs/architecture/ROLE_ACCESS_CONTROL.md → RBAC and permissions
- docs/design/05-components.md → Component inventory
- docs/design/07-animations.md → Animation system
- docs/design/08-theming.md → Theme configuration
- docs/design/tokens/tokens.json → Design tokens (machine-readable)

## Avoid
- Hardcoded color values
- any types in TypeScript
- Modifying shadcn/ui base components directly
- Adding unnecessary dependencies
- Inline styles
- Files outside established directory structure
